      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. You mentioned \"hidden risks\" and \"trap doors\" earlier. Are there any other subtle ways these clauses can be worded that might catch a freelancer off guard? Like, are there certain sneaky patterns I should be looking for in the text to avoid being blindsided by unexpected costs later?",
      "source": "evaluator"
